Read data

words <- read_csv("task/task-src/words.csv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   cond.no = col_integer(),
##   word = col_character(),
##   ipa = col_character(),
##   c1phonation = col_character(),
##   vowel = col_character(),
##   height = col_character(),
##   backness = col_character(),
##   roundness = col_character(),
##   consonant2 = col_character(),
##   manner = col_character(),
##   place = col_character(),
##   aspiration = col_character(),
##   syllables = col_character(),
##   syl_structure = col_character(),
##   gloss = col_character(),
##   pos = col_character(),
##   comp = col_character(),
##   contx = col_character()
## )
stops <- read_csv(
    "results/results.csv",
    na = "--undefined--"
    ) %>%
    right_join(y = words) %>%
    mutate(
        syllables = factor(syllables, c("mono","di")),
        vowel = factor(vowel, c("i", "", "", "e", "", "a", "o", "ei", "ai", "ou")),
        syl_structure = factor(syl_structure, c("cvcc", "vcc", "cvvcc", "vvcc", "cvccv", "cvvccv"))
        ) %>%
    filter(syl_structure %in% c("cvcc", "cvccv")) %>%
    mutate_if(is.character, as.factor) %>%
    filter(manner == "stop", contx == "cc") %>%
    droplevels()
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   speaker = col_character(),
##   index = col_integer(),
##   word = col_character(),
##   time = col_double(),
##   word.dur = col_double(),
##   voicing.dur = col_double(),
##   vowel.dur = col_double(),
##   cluster.dur = col_double(),
##   spreading.dur = col_double(),
##   sonorant.dur = col_double(),
##   closure.dur = col_double(),
##   vor = col_double(),
##   voffr = col_double(),
##   mor = col_double()
## )
## Joining, by = "word"

LMER

Vowel duration

vowel.lmer <- lmer(
    vowel.dur ~
        aspiration *
        syl_structure +
        vowel +
        c1phonation +
        vor +
        (1|word) +
        (1+aspiration|speaker),
    data = stops)

summary(vowel.lmer)

There is an iteraction between aspiration and syllable structure: the effect of aspiration is stronger in CVCC words then in CVCCV words.

plot(allEffects(vowel.lmer.2))

plot(fitted(vowel.lmer), resid(vowel.lmer))

        aspiration *
        syl_structure +

CVCC words are shorter if CC is pre-aspirated, while this does not happen with CVCCV words. However, CVCCV words show a bimodal distribution I dont know how to explain.

Main effects and interaction plots

vowel.ef <- as.data.frame(
    effect("aspiration:syl_structure", vowel.lmer)
) %>%
    mutate(aspiration = recode(aspiration, no = "unaspirated", yes = "preaspirated"),
           syl_structure = recode(syl_structure, cvcc = "CVCC", "cvccv" = "CVCCV")
    )

vowel.ef %>%
    ggplot(aes(aspiration, fit)) +
    geom_errorbar(aes(ymin=fit-se, ymax=fit+se), width=0.2, colour = "#754F9B") +
    geom_point(size = 3) +
    facet_grid(. ~ syl_structure) +
    labs(y = "vowel duration (msec)") +
    theme(strip.background = element_rect(colour = "#754F9B", fill = "#754F9B"))

word.ef <- as.data.frame(
    effect("aspiration:syl_structure", word.lmer)
) %>%
    mutate(aspiration = recode(aspiration, no = "unaspirated", yes = "preaspirated"),
           syl_structure = recode(syl_structure, cvcc = "CVCC", cvccv = "CVCCV")
    )

word.ef %>%
    ggplot(aes(aspiration, fit)) +
    geom_errorbar(aes(ymin=fit-se, ymax=fit+se), width=0.2, colour = "#754F9B") +
    geom_point(size = 3) +
    facet_grid(. ~ syl_structure) +
    labs(y = "word duration (msec)") +
    theme(strip.background = element_rect(colour = "#754F9B", fill = "#754F9B"))

voicing.ef <- as.data.frame(
    effect("aspiration", voicing.lmer)
) %>%
    mutate(aspiration = recode(aspiration, no = "unaspirated", yes = "preaspirated"))

voicing.ef %>%
    ggplot(aes(aspiration, fit)) +
    geom_errorbar(aes(ymin=fit-se, ymax=fit+se), width=0.1, colour = "#754F9B") +
    geom_point(size = 3.5) +
    labs(y = "voicing duration (msec)")
